  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a comprehensive observational study of clinical pump operation under real CPB conditions, which the assessment narrative treats as functionally equivalent to controlled experimental testing. The hemolysis index measurements collected during routine clinical monitoring are cited extensively as satisfying the validation requirement; however, the governing requirement mandates a controlled-experiment methodology, whereas the supporting activity was conducted as an observational study without experimental intervention or randomisation.",
