      "name": "Hemolysis validation — controlled-experiment requirement",
      "description": "The validation activity supporting the CFD hemolysis prediction shall employ a controlled-experiment methodology in which operating conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, inlet haematocrit) are systematically varied under laboratory-controlled conditions to isolate the effect of each parameter on the relative hemolysis index. Observational or retrospective clinical data collection does not satisfy this requirement because confounding patient-level variables cannot be controlled.",
      "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "RHI predicted by CFD must agree with controlled-experiment measurements within ±15% across all five nominated operating points."
    }
